Your function could only return true if the tree would have no leaf-nodes. B-Trees obviously have leaves.

Your `(node.children.length != 2)` condition suggests that you are working with dynamically sized `children` arrays, so I&#39;ll assume that when there are no children, the `children.length` is zero. 

So change to this:

```
private boolean isBinary(BNode node) {
    if (node.children.length == 0)
        return true; // Leaves are OK.
    if (node.children.length != 2)
        return false;
    else
        return (isBinary(node.children[0]) &amp;&amp; isBinary(node.children[1]));
}
```

Of course, if you have a different way to identify leaves, like with a different class that does not have a `children` field, then test for that condition instead. The essence is that you should detect when you are at a leaf and then always return true.

