1) It&#39;s caused by lacking of `getter` and `setter` methods in an amazon object bean.
2) By default , a setter method should start with `set` like `setPropName()`,but its&#39;not in amazon object bean.
3) Meanwhile ,Jackson-json required the getter/setter methods in the pattern of `getPropName`| `setPropName`. And this&#39;s where the crash happens.

4) How to fix this ?
Assuming we got an amazon object bean, `software.amazon.awssdk.services.organizations.model.Account`.

```java
final List&lt;Account&gt; accounts = response.accounts();
// call its toBuilder() method,
// and it returns a BuilderImpl ,which dose have standard getter/setter methods
List&lt;Account.Builder&gt; list = accounts.stream().map(a -&gt; a.toBuilder()).collect(Collectors.toList());
// this list now can be jackson serialized properly 
return list;
```
